Implement 'Add' and 'Delete' command
commitResults.messageBody:
- Refactor the previous AB3 add and delete command classes to
  AddAB3Command and DeleteAB3Command repectively. Refactor the previous
  abtract Command class to AB3Command.

- Write a new AddCommand and DeleteCommand class which both extend the
  new Command class. These to classes are able to add and delete
  student/module/class group from TAssist.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement ListCommand and update command parsers
commitResults.messageBody:
- Update ParserUtil to parser name, email and phone of a student rather
  than a person. Add methods to parse module name, module code, academic
  year, module index, class group id and class group type.

- List the students, modules or class groups based on the EntityType
  passed into ListCommand class.

- Refractor previous ListCommand.java, Parser.java,
  AddCommandParser.java, DeleteCommandParser.java to
  ListAB3Command.java, AB3Parser.java, AddAB3CommandParser.java and
  DeleteAB3CommandParser.java respectively.

- Implement Parser<T> interface to with a method parse that takes in a
  String of user input and Model as parameters and returns the generic
  type T. (It takes in a model because to add a class group, we need to
  find its module by the index provided by users, and the only way to
  get the corresponding module is using the getFilteredModuleList()
  method in Model class).

- Update parseCommand() method in TaAssistParser to include a Model as a
  parameter due to the same reason as above. Remove unnecessary commands
  in the switch clause.

- Add TYPE_STUDENT, TYPE_MODULE and TYPE_CLASS to CliSyntax for command
  parsing.
